data.entities: yellow cake mix | eggs | cream cheese | butter | confectioners sugar | lemon juice
data.sentence: 1 box yellow cake mix, 2 eggs, 1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese, softened, 1 stick butter or margarine, 1 (1 lb.) box confectioners sugar, 1/4 lemon juice Mix cake mix 1 egg and butter together. Press into bottom and side of pan (9 x 12-inch). Then mix cream cheese 1 egg confectioners sugar and lemon juice. Pour over mixture. Bake at 325\u00b0 for 50 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

data.entities: crescent rolls | cream cheese | mayo | crescent rolls
data.sentence: pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan. bake for 6 to 8 minutes. mix together cream cheese, dressing and mayo. top cooled crescent rolls. add remaining ingredients. refrigerate.

data.entities: confectioners sugar | peanut butter | butter | white confectioner coating
data.sentence: In a mixing bowl combine sugar and peanut butter mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Chill for 30 minutes or until firm. Meanwhile melt the white coating in a double boiler or microwave-safe bowl. Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden. Yields 2 dozen.

data.entities: cider vinegar | water | oil | sugar | salt | black pepper | pinto beans | garbanzo beans | white shoepeg corn | green chilies | pimiento | green bell pepper | celery | onion
data.sentence: 14 cup cider vinegar, 1 tablespoon water, 12 cup oil, 1 teaspoon sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 12 teaspoon black pepper, 15 ounces pinto beans, drained, 15 ounces garbanzo beans, drained, 2 (11 ounce) cans white shoepeg corn, drained, 2 (4 ounce) canschopped green chilies, drained, 2 ounces finely chopped pimiento, drained, 1 cup finely chopped green bell pepper, 1 cup finely chopped celery, 1 small onion, finely chopped Combine the vinegar water oil sugar salt and pepper in a saucepan. Bring to a boil stirring occasionally. Cool the marinade to room temperature. Combine the beans peas corn green chilies and pimiento in a large bowl. Add the green pepper celery and onion. Add the marinade; mix well. Chill covered for 24 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

data.entities: jello | boiling water | mayonnaise | peaches | peaches | pineapple | jello
data.sentence: dissolve jello in boiling water. add mayonnaise, stirring until dissolved. while this is cooling, peel and thinly slice peaches. place peaches and pineapple with juice in 8 x 8-inch pan. pour jello over fruit. chill until set.

data.entities: lean ground beef | spaghetti sauce | mozzarella cheese
data.sentence: 1 bag Pasta Accents garden herb seasoning, 3/4 lb. lean ground beef, 3/4 c. spaghetti sauce, 1/3 c. shredded Mozzarella cheese In large skillet brown lean ground beef. Add Pasta Accents and spaghetti sauce. Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top.

data.entities: ground beef | basil | oregano | onion soup | boiling water | tomato sauce | elbow macaroni | Parmesan cheese
data.sentence: 1 1/2 lb. ground beef, 1 tsp. basil, 1 tsp. oregano, 1 envelope onion soup mix, 6 c. boiling water, 1 (8 oz.) can tomato sauce, 1 c. elbow macaroni, Parmesan cheese Brown beef and drain excess fat. Add next 6 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in raw macaroni. Simmer for 30 minutes.

data.entities: graham cracker crumbs | margarine | Confectioners Sugar | butter | eggs | Vanilla | blueberry pie filling | pecans | sugar | sugar | flour
data.sentence: 8 oz. graham cracker crumbs, 4 oz. margarine, 1 box confectioners sugar, 8 oz. butter, 2 eggs, 1/2 tsp. vanilla, 4 c. blueberry pie filling, 1 large Cool Whip, 1 c. finely chopped pecans, 1 c. sugar, 1/4 c. sugar, 1/4 c. flour Beat confectioners sugar butter eggs and vanilla for 20 minutes. Pour over graham cracker crust then pour 4 cups blueberry pie filling over butter egg and sugar mixture. Then make top layer of large Cool Whip and 1 cup finely chopped pecans. Cook blueberries 30 minutes with 1 cup sugar. Then add a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour to blueberries.

data.entities: pecans | pecans
data.sentence: have cheeses at room temperature. put all ingredients with the exception of the pecans into a mixer and mix well. refrigerate until firm. roll into a ball and roll in pecans until well coated. wrap in foil or plastic and let ripen in refrigerator for at least 24 hours. leave at room temperature for 2 hours before serving. serve with crisp crackers.

data.entities: egg | corn | milk | sugar | Cheddar cheese | jalapeno pepper
data.sentence: Preheat oven to 450\u00b0. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Combine all ingredients in order listed blend well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 9 servings.

data.entities: margarine | Crisco | brown sugar | white sugar | vanilla | egg | flour | baking soda | cream of tartar | salt | nuts
data.sentence: 1/2 c. margarine, 1/2 c. Crisco, 1/2 c. brown sugar, 1/2 c. white sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, 1 egg, 2 1/2 c. flour, 1 tsp. baking soda, 1 tsp. cream of tartar, 1/4 tsp. salt, 1/2 c. nuts (optional) Mix all together and form cookie balls. Press each down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350\u00b0 for 10 to 12 minutes.

data.entities: shortening | sugar | honey | egg | flour | salt | oats | raisins
data.sentence: 3/4 c. shortening, 3/4 c. granulated sugar, 1/2 c. honey, 1 egg, 1 1/4 c. flour, 1/2 tsp. salt, 2 c. quick oats, 1 c. seedless raisins Cream together shortening sugar honey and egg; stir in flour soda salt and oats; beat well. Add raisins. Drop by tablespoonful on greased baking sheets. Bake above oven center at 375\u00b0 for 8 to 10 minutes or until evenly browned. Let stand on sheets 2 to 3 minutes. Remove and cool. Makes about 36 cookies.

data.entities: mix | baking | mix | sugar | orange | margarine
data.sentence: heat oven to 400°. mix baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar and the orange peel. cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. press mixture in bottom of ungreased round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch. bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. cool about 30 minutes.

data.entities: oil | pepper | garlic | salt | pepper | vinegar | bread | garlic | olive | oil | mozzarella cheese | basil
data.sentence: heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. add the pepper strips and saute until lightly browned at the edges and beginning to soften, about 5 minutes. reduce the heat to medium low, stir in the minced garlic, cover and continue cooking until soft, about 8 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. season with salt and pepper to taste; remove from heat and stir in the vinegar. grill the bread over a medium heat, turning once, until golden brown on both sides, 1 to 2 minutes. place the toast slices on a large platter, rub the peeled garlic over the tops, and brush with the remaining olive oil. place a few slices of mozzarella cheese on each toast. cover with a portion of the sauteed peppers, the top with a sprinkling of basil. serve immediately.

data.entities: green onions | butter | flour | cayenne pepper | milk | dressing | catsup | crab | crab | asparagus
data.sentence: cook green onions in butter until tender. stir in flour and cayenne pepper. add milk. stir until thickened. remove from heat. stir in ranch dressing, catsup and crab. heat, but do not cook. spoon warm crab over cooked asparagus. sprinkle with parmesan. broil 3 to 4 minutes (until lightly browned). serve over toast. (an attractive and easy dish for company.)

data.entities: flour tortillas | Serrano ham | grated cheese | scallion | vegetable oil
data.sentence: 1 (6 inch) soft flour tortillas, 2 slices serrano ham or 2 slices prosciutto, preferred, 14-12 cup grated cheese, any type you like, 12 scallion, sliced fine, 3 -4 slices pickled jalapeno peppers, minced (from a jar), 1 teaspoon vegetable oil Preheat a stovetop griddle or skillet. Place ham over the entire surface of the tortilla. Cover 1/2 the surface with cheese scallion and jalapeno. Fold tortilla over. Brush both sides with oil. Place on griddle (or skillet) and cook until grill marks appear (or it turns brown) 1-2 minutes per side. Cut into 3-4 wedges and serve.

data.entities: macaroni shells | green onions | bacon bits | Mayonnaise | lemon juice | parmesan cheese | sugar | garlic powder | bite size salad greens | zucchini | cauliflowerets | broccoli flowerets | tomatoes
data.sentence: 1 (7 to 8 oz.) pkg. macaroni shells, 1/2 c. sliced green onions, 1/2 c. bacon bits, 1 c. mayonnaise, 1/4 c. lemon juice, 3 tsp. grated Parmesan cheese, 1 tsp. sugar, 1/2 tsp. garlic powder, 4 c. bite size salad greens, 1 medium zucchini, sliced, 1 c. sliced cauliflowerets, 1 c. broccoli flowerets, 2 medium tomatoes, cut into wedges Cook macaroni as per package directions and drain. Rinse with cold water; drain again. Stir together macaroni onions and bacon bits in medium bowl. Mix mayonnaise lemon juice cheese sugar and garlic powder. In 3 1/2-quart salad bowl layer salad greens macaroni mixture zucchini and cauliflowerets. On top of this layer broccoli and tomatoes. Pour dressing evenly over top. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Sprinkle with bacon bits just before serving. Refrigerate only remaining salad. Makes 10 servings.

data.entities: gin | liqueur | sage
data.sentence: 1 34 ounces premium gin, 14 ounce green chartreuse liqueur, 2 fresh sage leaves, ice In a cocktail shaker filled with ice add gin and chartreuse. Stir until well chilled. Run a fresh sage leaf around the rim of a martini glass. Strain alcohol into martini glass and garnish with a fresh sage leaf. Enjoy!

data.entities: nuts | Cheerios | rice squares | pretzel bites | salad oil | Worcestershire sauce | garlic salt | seasoning salt
data.sentence: 2 lb. mixed salted nuts, 10 1/2 oz. pkg. Cheerios, 6 1/2 oz. pkg. rice squares, 6 1/2 oz. pkg. pretzel bites, 5 1/2 oz. stem pretzel sticks, 2 c. salad oil, 2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce, 1 tsp. garlic salt, 1 tsp. seasoning salt Mix oil and sauce together. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 250\u00b0 for 2 hours stirring every 15 minutes. Store in cans tins jars or plastic bags.

data.entities: vanilla | egg whites | sugar | cornstarch | vanilla | butter | milk | vanilla | powdered sugar | peanut butter | vanilla | egg whites | sugar | peanut butter
data.sentence: make vanilla filling: set aside the egg whites. cook 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, vanilla, butter and milk until thick, pour half of the vanilla filling in a deep dish pie shell and set aside. then take powdered sugar and peanut butter, mix until crumbly, pour 3/4 cup of crumbs on filling. pour remaining vanilla filling on top of crust. beat egg whites until peaks form. add 2 tablespoons sugar, beat until stiff. spread on pie. put remaining peanut butter crumbs on top of pie. cook at 325° until brown.

data.entities: chicken | egg | Katakuriko | milk | ketchup | soy sauce | Curry | Pepper | mayonnaise
data.sentence: 1 Chicken breast, 1 Egg, 1/2 tbsp Katakuriko, 1 tbsp Milk, 2 tbsp Ketchup, 1/2 tbsp Soy sauce, 1/2 tsp Curry powder, 1 dash Pepper, 1 Mayonnaise Cut the chicken breast in half lengthwise and slice diagonally into pieces. Pound with a rolling pin and make it thinner. This helps the chicken become tender. Add the ingredients into a plastic bag and rub everything together to mix. Add the chicken breast from Step 1 and marinate for at least 1 hour in the fridge. Combine the ingredients in a bowl. Add in the marinated chicken and mix in the beaten egg. Heat up a frying pan. Swirl on some mayonnaise instead of oil to grease the pan and fry the chicken breast from Step 3.
